    <section class="page-intro">
        <p>
            Cincinnati, often called the "Queen City," is a vibrant and historic city in Ohio.
            Incorporated in 1819, it has grown to a population of over 300,000.
            Cincinnati is known for its rich cultural heritage, diverse neighborhoods, and significant contributions to
            arts, sports, and industry.
            The city is home to major league sports teams, including the Cincinnati Bengals and the Cincinnati Reds,
            America's first professional baseball team.
            Cincinnati also boasts a thriving arts scene, with institutions like the Cincinnati Art Museum and the
            Cincinnati Symphony Orchestra.
        </p>
    </section>


